  <!-- INTRODUCTION -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">Introduction to Cooker Installation</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Installing a new electric cooker is a vital step in upgrading your kitchen, ensuring both safety and optimal performance from your new appliance. Whether you've chosen an electric cooker, a gas cooker, or a dual fuel cooker, proper cooker installation is essential to protect your investment and maintain the manufacturer's guarantee.
      </p>
      <p>
        The installation process involves more than simply connecting wires—it requires careful attention to power supply, wiring, and proper ventilation to prevent hazards and ensure efficient operation. By hiring a professional electrician, you can be confident that your new electric cooker will be installed safely, in compliance with all regulations, and ready to deliver reliable cooking results for years to come.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CHOOSING THE RIGHT COOKER -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">Choosing the Right Cooker</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Selecting the right cooker is the foundation of a successful cooker installation. With a wide range of options available—including electric cookers, gas cookers, dual fuel cookers, built-in ovens, and range cookers—it's important to consider your kitchen layout, cooking habits, and budget.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Electric cookers are popular for their straightforward installation and compatibility with modern kitchens, but may require a dedicated circuit. Gas cookers offer precise heat control but must be installed by a Gas Safe registered engineer. Dual fuel cookers combine the best of both worlds, offering electric ovens with gas hobs for versatile cooking.
      </p>
      <p>
        Understanding the installation process and circuit requirements for each type of cooker will help you make an informed choice and ensure your new appliance fits seamlessly into your kitchen.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PREPARATION FOR INSTALLATION -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">Preparation for Installation</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Proper preparation is key to a smooth and efficient cooker installation. Before your new electric cooker arrives, make sure the installation area is clear of any obstructions and that there is adequate space for the appliance.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Check that the power supply is accessible and that the location allows for proper ventilation, which is essential for safe operation. If you're replacing an existing appliance, ensure it is fully disconnected and removed, and have your new appliance unpacked and ready for installation.
      </p>
      <p>
        A professional installation service can provide expert advice on preparing your kitchen, helping you choose the best location for your cooker and ensuring all safety requirements are met before the installation process begins.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

