      <p class="mb-6">
        Having the right tools and materials on hand is essential for a safe and efficient electric cooker installation. Key items include a cooker control unit, an isolating switch, and the appropriate wiring materials to match your appliance's requirements.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-6">
        It's also important to have the manufacturer's instructions and any relevant safety guidelines available during the installation process. While some homeowners may be tempted to tackle installation themselves, working with a professional electrician ensures that all connections are made safely and in compliance with regulations.
      </p>
      <p>
        A qualified professional will bring the necessary expertise, tools, and materials to complete the installation to the highest standard, giving you peace of mind and a fully functional cooker.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

